SUMMARY:Rembrandt Chamber Musicians: The Trout with Henry Kramer
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T150000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260315T170000
UID:250905GLtR8Ib8gES3-5CvJtASPg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/VJiaNANWs0ibR73gK1Etqw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Rembrandt Chamber Musicians welcomes renowned guest artists He
 nry Kramer\, piano\, and Sam Shuhan\, double bass\, for a program of lush 
 Romantic masterpieces. The evening begins with Fauré’s dramatic and ten
 der Piano Quartet in C minor\, a work of lyrical elegance and emotional de
 pth. Schubert’s beloved “Trout” Quintet follows\, brimming with char
 m\, warmth\, and the composer’s signature melodic brilliance.\n\nArtists
 : John Macfarlane\, violin\; Carol Cook\, viola\; Calum Cook\, cello\; Sam
  Shuhan\, double bass\; Henry Kramer\, piano\n\nFauré: Piano Quartet in C
  minor\, Op. 15\n\nSchubert: Piano Quintet in A major D. 667
LOCATION:Nichols Concert Hall
