END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Cityspark Evanston": "https://www.evanstonartcenter.org/exhibitions/woundwomb-ruth-poor"}
X-SOURCE-ID:cityspark_evanston
SUMMARY:Beatrice | Ruth Poor
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T090000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260316T160000
UID:260217JST3VRqUtUCwCo1rysYqVQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/LWznMwws6U-NK01KN5n0gA.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:On view February 21 - March 18\, 2026\n\nOpening Reception Su
 nday\, February 22\, 2026\, 1-4 pm\n\nRuth L. Poor\, raised in Indiana\, u
 ses their work to dissect memories of the rural Midwest and to investigate
  intersections between power\, American history\, faith\, and deviancy. Po
 or received their MFA from the Painting & Drawing department at the School
  of the Art Institute of Chicago \\(SAIC\\) and completed their B.A. in St
 udio Art and Religious Studies at Cornell College and DePauw University. T
 hey currently reside in Chicago\, Illinois\, where they teach at SAIC\, No
 rth Central College\, and College of DuPage\, and teach/advise with the Pr
 ison \\+ Neighborhood Arts Project. They have shown work nationally and in
 ternationally at venues such as the University ofChicago \\[Chicago\, IL\\
 ]\, Secrist|Beach Gallery \\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, the New York Academy of Art
  \\[New York\, NY\\]\, Zolla/Lieberman Gallery\\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, Art EXP
 O \\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, The Green Gallery \\[Milwaukee\, WI\\]\, ADDS DONNA
  Gallery \\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, Manifest Gallery\\[Cincinnati\, OH\\]\, Woma
 n Made Gallery \\[Chicago\, IL\\]\, and Indiana University \\[Bloomington\
 , IN\\]. They are also a current Artist-in-Residence with the Chicago Arti
 st Coalition \\(2024-2026\\).
LOCATION:Evanston Art Center
URL:https://www.evanstonartcenter.org/exhibitions/woundwomb-ruth-poor
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"First Presbyterian": "https://firstpresevanston.org/event/lenten-small-group-march-16/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:first_presbyterian
X-SOURCE:First Presbyterian
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260316T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260316T110000
DTSTAMP:20260314T212905
CREATED:20260219T162820Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T162820Z
UID:44611-1773653400-1773658800@firstpresevanston.org
SUMMARY:Lenten Small Group March 16
DESCRIPTION:This is the fourth of five meetings taking place at FPCE on Mondays during Lent. This ‘pop-up’ small group is forming for those interested in using the lectio divina and visio divina methods to contemplate the Bible passage that is the topic of each week’s sermon and a related piece of art. This group will meet during Lent on Mondays at 9:30 a.m.\, both in person in Room 213 and on Zoom. All are welcome to join this peaceful opportunity to meditate on Scripture. Contact Valrie Barrett valrie924@gmail.com or Beth Rice rice.beth.l@gmail.com for details on how to take part. \nWant to join on Zoom? Join here: https://us06web.zoom.us/j/85398693001?pwd=TfbcLXibwYbfJfKvFYmPmBWdZulVaj.1 \nWhat’s a ‘pop-up’ group? \nA pop-up group is one that is only around for a short time or a specific season (it pops up and then it’s gone). These are open to anyone\, and are especially terrific for those who are new to First Pres Evanston\, or are not currently involved in one of our small groups.
URL:https://firstpresevanston.org/event/lenten-small-group-march-16/
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Evanston\, 1427 Chicago Avenue Evanston\, IL\, 60201\, United States
CATEGORIES:Featured Event,Small Group
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://firstpresevanston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/LentBibleGroup_800x600EventTile.jpg
END:VEVENT
