DESCRIPTION:A League of Their Own“There’s no crying in baseball!” Dir
 ected by Penny Marshall\, this sports dramedy is a fictionalized story of 
 the All-American Girls Professional Baseball League. It’s set in 1943 an
 d focuses on The Rockford Peaches\, an all-girl baseball team from Rockfor
 d\, IL. They are a disparate group\, with varying talents\, and their man
 ager Jimmy Dugan (Tom Hanks) is cynical and abrasive at first. However\, t
 he women are determined to make something of the team\, to step out of ste
 reotypical and traditional roles. Their enthusiasm has a positive effect o
 n the manager. He becomes the manager the team needs and they\, whether wi
 n or lose\, know much was accomplished.  Starring Tom Hanks\, Geena Davi
 s\, Rosie O'Donnell\, Madonna.1992 : 128 minutes : PG for language: Comedy
 Free tickets will be given to those who attend.Watch the trailer for A Lea
 gue of Their Own.Find A League of Their Own in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Movie
