X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Morton Grove Library": "https://www.mgpl.org/event/indie-lens-pop-inquisitor-64314"}
X-SOURCE-ID:morton_grove_library
X-SOURCE:Morton Grove Library
UID:64314
DTSTAMP:20260315T025449Z
SUMMARY:Indie Lens Pop-Up: The Inquisitor
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.mgpl.org/event/indie-lens-pop-inquisitor-64314
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260107T211246Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260108T171510Z
DESCRIPTION:Explore the life and legacy of Barbara Jordan in The Inquisito
 r. Jordan was a groundbreaking Texas congresswoman whose sharp intellect a
 nd moral clarity transformed U.S. politics. From Nixon’s impeachment to 
 civil rights battles\, her voice demanded accountability\, while she priva
 tely faced struggles few ever knew of. (2025\, NR\, 1hr 35min) About Indi
 e Lens Pop-UpIndie Lens Pop-Up is a community series that brings people to
 gether for film screenings and conversations. Featuring documentaries seen
  on PBS's Independent Lens\, Indie Lens Pop-Up draws local residents\, le
 aders\, and organizations to discuss what matters most. For more informati
 on\, visit pbs.org/indielenspopup.
CATEGORIES:Movie
CONTACT:Adult & Teen Services\, info@mgpl.org\, 8479295101
DTSTART:20260318T230000Z
DTEND:20260319T003000Z
LOCATION:6140 Lincoln Avenue\, Morton Grove\, IL\, 60053\, US
ROOM:Baxter Auditorium
END:VEVENT
