SUMMARY:Between the Lines: Sandwich by Catherine Newman
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.mgpl.org/event/between-lines-tbd-61628
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20250909T160457Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260108T171604Z
DESCRIPTION:Between the Lines is now held on two different days\, either in
  person or on Zoom. Titles are always available on Hoopla\, as well as ot
 her library ebook platforms. New members are warmly welcome! Book Synopsi
 s: From the beloved author of We All Want Impossible Things and Wreck\, a
  moving\, hilarious story of a family summer vacation full of secrets\, lu
 nch\, and learning to let go.For the past two decades\, Rocky has looked f
 orward to her family’s yearly escape to Cape Cod. Their humble beach-tow
 n rental has been the site of sweet memories\, sunny days\, great meals\, 
 and messes of all kinds: emotional\, marital\, and—thanks to the cottage
 ’s ancient plumbing—septic too.This year’s vacation\, with Rocky san
 dwiched between her half-grown kids and fully aging parents\, promises to 
 be just as delightful as summers past—except\, perhaps\, for Rocky’s h
 ormonal bouts of rage and melancholy. (Hello\, menopause!) Her body is cha
 nging—her life is\, too. And then a chain of events sends Rocky into the
  past\, reliving both the tenderness and sorrow of a handful of long-ago s
 ummers.It's one precious week: everything is in balance\; everything is in
  flux. And when Rocky comes face to face with her family’s history and f
 uture\, she is forced to accept that she can no longer hide her secrets fr
 om the people she loves.
CATEGORIES:Books & Authors
CONTACT:Adult Services\, info@mgpl.org\, 8479654220
DTSTART:20260319T150000Z
DTEND:20260319T160000Z
LOCATION:6140 Lincoln Avenue\, Morton Grove\, IL\, 60053\, US
ROOM:Baxter Auditorium
END:VEVENT
