X-SOURCE-ID:cityspark_evanston
SUMMARY:Iran and U.S. Imperialism
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T143000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T163000
UID:2603148d04wJyYI060lGpOk4ag5A
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/713287c2-ea40-46d9-9bd5-2e196e6c0bac.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Daniel Immerwahr\, award winning professor of U.S. history at 
 Northwestern University\, will lecture on the context of the U.S./Israeli 
 war in Iran. Author of the influential book\, How to Hide and Empire\, Imm
 erwahr is known both for his trenchant analysis and for his wit. Refreshme
 nts will be served. The talk will be followed by question and answers\, as
  well as group discussion. It is free and open to the public. Attendees ar
 e encouraged to RSVP at tinyurl.com/CAPA-March-21.
LOCATION:Evanston Public Library\, Community Room
URL:http://tinyurl.com/CAPA-March-21
