BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"First Presbyterian": "https://firstpresevanston.org/event/march-22-sunday-worship-service/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:first_presbyterian
X-SOURCE:First Presbyterian
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260322T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260322T113000
DTSTAMP:20260314T212905
CREATED:20260219T161918Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260302T184545Z
UID:44605-1774175400-1774179000@firstpresevanston.org
SUMMARY:Sunday Worship Service
DESCRIPTION:Worship This Sunday \nThe Book of Job: Broken Hallelujahs\n“Why?”\nSunday\, March 22\, 2026\n10:30 a.m. in the Sanctuary & Online \nThis Sunday\, we continue our Lenten sermon series\, The Book of Job: Broken Hallelujahs\, a journey through the raw\, honest faith of Job. Senior Pastor Derek Zeyl will preach from Job 42\, where Job encounters God’s overwhelming presence and responds with humility\, trust\, and a renewed understanding of God’s goodness\, even without receiving the tidy “why” he longed for. \nWhat to Expect\n\nSpirit-led worship with Scripture\, song\, and prayer\nA thoughtful\, engaging sermon rooted in the teachings of Jesus\nChildren’s and Youth programs available during the service\nFellowship Hour upstairs following worship\n\nScripture for This Sunday\nJob 42 \n\nA chapter where Job moves from questioning to surrender\, discovering that God’s wisdom holds more than easy explanations ever could and that restoration begins with relationship.\n\nJoin Us on Sunday\nWe’d love to worship with you\, whether in person or online. If you’re visiting for the first time\, welcome! We hope you’ll feel at home as we gather to seek God together\, bring our honest questions\, and discover the hope woven through Job’s story and our own.
URL:https://firstpresevanston.org/event/march-22-sunday-worship-service/
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Evanston\, 1427 Chicago Avenue Evanston\, IL\, 60201\, United States
CATEGORIES:Featured Event,Worship Service
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://firstpresevanston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/worshipService800x600.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Beth Emet": "https://bethemet.org/event/conversational-hebrew/2026-03-22/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:beth_emet
X-SOURCE:Beth Emet
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260322T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260322T120000
DTSTAMP:20260314T215458
CREATED:20251016T010050Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251208T204045Z
UID:10021398-1774177200-1774180800@bethemet.org
SUMMARY:Conversational Hebrew
DESCRIPTION:Conversational Hebrew meets most Sundays\, 11:00 am–12:00 pm when Beit Sefer meets. This class uses an Ulpan-like immersive setting to teach modern conversational Hebrew. Participants will read news articles\, discuss life and current events\, and other basic conversations in Hebrew. The only prerequisite is basic Hebrew skills. The class meets in the Beit Midrash. \nMembers\, click here to register. \nGuests\, click here to register. \nDorit Flatt is the daughter of Holocaust survivors and grew up in Tel-Aviv\, Israel. After completing her IDF service in the paratrooper unit\, she studied elementary education at Seminar Levinsky in Tel-Aviv. She holds a BA in Psychology from the University of Michigan and taught Hebrew language\, literature\, and religious studies in Michigan for 25 years.
URL:https://bethemet.org/event/conversational-hebrew/2026-03-22/
CATEGORIES:Adult Programming
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bethemet.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Adult-Hebrew.jpg
END:VEVENT
