BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/meet-me-moment-1965"}
X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:1965
DTSTAMP:20260315T025447Z
SUMMARY:Meet Me in a Moment
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/meet-me-moment-1965
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20250807T173549Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251229T164446Z
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy the music of four great Jewish composers and learn about 
 their lives and works. Each musical selection for violin and piano is foll
 owed by a historically informed\, theatrical scene from the composer's lif
 e. Written and directed by Aviva Chertok Li\, this one-of-a-kind productio
 n will bring you the best of Jewish classical music while immersing you in
  Jewish history and culture.Step back in time to Cleveland of the 1920’s
  and the living room of composer Ernest Bloch\, join a rehearsal at the Je
 rusalem Academy of Music with Paul Ben-Haim\, and attend a meeting of the 
 Society of Jewish Folk Music in St. Petersburg with Lazare Saminsky. Meet 
 one of America’s greatest modern Jewish composers\, through a special vi
 deo screening of violinist Aviva Chertok Li's interview with Grammy-nomina
 ted composer\, Jonathan Leshnoff. Free tickets will be given to those pre
 sent starting at 2:30 pm.
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
DTSTART:20260322T200000Z
DTEND:20260322T211500Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Petty Auditorium
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
