BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/we-native-people-17960"}
X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:17960
DTSTAMP:20260315T025447Z
SUMMARY:We The Native People
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/we-native-people-17960
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251216T194307Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260126T220440Z
DESCRIPTION:How did the signing of the Declaration of Independence affect t
 he Native American people? How did the government and its people view Nati
 ve Americans\, and what were the consequences of those views? Kim Sigafus 
 will discuss the impact the Declaration of Independence had on the lives o
 f the Native people and what ultimately was lost. She will cover how the N
 ative people once lived\, worked the land\, and raised their children\, an
 d explain what was lost of their culture as western expansion took place. 
 You will have the chance to learn music\, drum\, sing\, and play Native Am
 erican instruments. Traditional foods will also be discussed\, and a recip
 e will be handed out. Kim Sigafus is an award-winning Ojibwa author who w
 rites Native American fiction\, nonfiction\, children’s\, and young adul
 t books. She has presented on Native history\, food\, and music\, and has 
 traveled all over the Midwest in her native regalia\, bringing Native cult
 ure to life. Kim’s family is from White Earth Reservation\, located in t
 he northwest corner of Minnesota.Keyword: USA 250
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture,Books and Authors
DTSTART:20260323T230000Z
DTEND:20260324T000000Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Radmacher Room
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Lincolnwood Library": "https://www.lincolnwoodlibrary.org/event/rescheduled-words-change-lives-conversation-chicago-books-women-prison-r-35353"}
X-SOURCE-ID:lincolnwood_library
X-SOURCE:Lincolnwood Library
UID:35353
DTSTAMP:20260315T025451Z
SUMMARY:*RESCHEDULED* Words That Change Lives: A Conversation with Chicago 
 Books to Women in Prison (R)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.lincolnwoodlibrary.org/event/rescheduled-words-ch
 ange-lives-conversation-chicago-books-women-prison-r-35353
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260310T220945Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260310T234835Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an inspiring evening that explores the power of boo
 ks to heal\, connect\, and transform lives. In partnership with Chicago Bo
 oks to Women in Prison\, we’ll learn how access to reading supports educ
 ation\, reflection\, escape\, and much more for women and trans people who
  are incarcerated. Volunteers from the organization will share their exper
 iences sending books to readers behind bars\, and we’ll hear from someon
 e who will share how the program supported them during their time in priso
 n and beyond.
CATEGORIES:Adult Learning
DTSTART:20260323T233000Z
DTEND:20260324T010000Z
LOCATION:4000 W. Pratt Ave.\, Lincolnwood\, IL\, 60712\, US
ROOM:Meeting Room C
GEO:42.0047721;-87.7292067
END:VEVENT
