BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Evanston Writers": "https://www.meetup.com/evanstonwriters/events/313405151/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_evanston_writers
X-SOURCE:Meetup Evanston Writers
UID:event_313405151@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260315T025500Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260326T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260326T210000
SUMMARY:Evanston Writers’ Workshop Long Development Group--meeting
DESCRIPTION:Evanston Writers Workshop\nHowdy all\,\n\nCongratulations to Marcia Harris – the newest submission to the Evanston Writers’ Workshop Long Development Group.\n\nLong Development Group mission blurb is to provide feedback and critique of a longer\, more developed piece of 10\,000 to 30\,000 words. To remind those interested in participating: the goal of this group is to analyze and give more overview-type feedback (e.g.\, plot\, premise\, structure\, consistent voice\, etc.)\n\n\\*new\\*\nAuthors are encouraged to write a full summary of their submissions/project’s plot\, this can be abstracted bullet points if needed. (circa 500 words.)\nFeel to include the mission of the piece. What is the X\, Y and Z of this story? Feel free to include tropes\, inspirations\, or the ontological motivations for the why this story exists. (circa 500 words. summary/motivations do not count against the 30\,000 word limit.)\n\nPlease include all questions that you would like to be answered. What do you want us to read for? What do you think is a particular weakness of the work\, are you trying to develop a subplot\, any motifs\, things like that. Maximum 20 questions\, try to make the questions as in-depth as possible.\n\n--For those who wish to read it and comment on Marcia's submission (whether or not you are able to come to the meeting)\, you can access it here:\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/15ZOuWzwnYDFPOYYawmpbfnO3e83To3vM/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=100821020442953994836&rtpof=true&sd=true\n\nOur in-person discussion of Marcia's piece will\nMeeting location and time March the 26th\, 7:00 p.m. In the lobby of the Orrington Hotel\, 1710 Orrington Avenue.\n\nWe look forward to your joining the nest Developmental Group meeting!
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/evanstonwriters/events/313405151/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260218T002224Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260218T002224Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/7/b/4/600_530418356.jpeg
END:VEVENT
