 o the public\, and an offering will be collected with 50% going to the per
 former and the other half supporting St. Mark’s Piano and Organ Fund. Th
 e concert will be followed with a festive reception in the Parlor. Everyon
 e is welcome! For more information\, please get in touch with Westley at m
 usic@stmarksevanston.org. Following the concert\, there will be a festival
  reception for all in our parlor.\n\nDetails: St. Mark’s Episcopal Churc
 h \\(1509 Ridge Ave\, Evanston\\). Parking is limited to street parking\, 
 but plenty is within walking distance. \n\nMeet the performer:\n\nAmethys
 t Winds is a woodwind quintet that calls St. Mark’s home. Members includ
 e: Lauren Moldenhauer \\(flute\\)\, Claire Bravo Cutting \\(oboe\\)\, West
 ley Art Hodges \\(clarinet\\)\, Walter van Gieson \\(bassoon\\)\, Connor C
 owart \\(french horn\\). More information about the ensemble can be found 
 on their website: www.amethystwinds.org
