SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260315T025500Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260329T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260329T160000
SUMMARY:#113: The Seven Daughters of Dupree by Nikesha Elise Williams
DESCRIPTION:Black Girls Read Book Club\n**Our March book selection is *The Seven Daughters of Dupree* by Chicago native Nikesha Elise Williams!** We will meet at [Zora's Place](https://www.zorasplace.com/)\, Evanston's only Black woman-owned bookshop.\n\nAbout the book: It’s 1995\, and fourteen-year-old Tati is determined to uncover the identity of her father. But her mother\, Nadia\, keeps her secrets close\, while her grandmother Gladys remains silent about the family’s past\, including why she left Land’s End\, Alabama\, in 1953. As Tati digs deeper\, she uncovers a legacy of family secrets\, where every generation of Dupree women has posed more questions than answers.\n\nFrom Jubi in 1917\, whose attempt to pass for white ends when she gives birth to Ruby\; to Ruby’s fiery lust for Sampson in 1934 that leads to a baby of her own\; to the night in 1980 that changed Nadia’s future forever\, the Dupree women carry the weight of their heritage. Bound by a mysterious malediction that means they will only give birth to daughters\, the Dupree women confront a legacy of pain\, resilience\, and survival that began with an enslaved ancestor who risked everything for freedom.\n\n*The Seven Daughters of Dupree* masterfully weaves together themes of generational trauma\, Black women’s resilience\, and unbreakable familial bonds. Nikesha Elise Williams delivers a feminist literary fiction that explores the ripple effects of actions\, secrets\, and love through seven generations of Black women.\n\n***The Seven Daughters of Dupree* will be released in January 2026 and is available for pre-order now. Support Zora's Place by purchasing your book at [their brick-and-mortar storefront](https://www.zorasplace.com/) or [their online storefront on Bookshop](https://bookshop.org/a/5326/9781668051948).**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/black-girls-read-book-club/events/312310442/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251205T040325Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251205T040325Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/4/4/3/600_531809763.jpeg
END:VEVENT
