BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Oakton College": "https://events.oakton.edu/event/religious-studies-speaker-series-brett-hendrickson"}
X-SOURCE-ID:oakton_college
X-SOURCE:Oakton College
CATEGORIES:Speaker Series,Religious Studies Speaker Series
DESCRIPTION:Miraculous Earth: The Santuario de Chimayó\n\n \n\nNorthern New
  Mexico boasts dozens of colonial-era adobe churches\, most built by Pueblo
  and Hispano hands under the watchful guidance of Spanish Franciscan friars
 . Each is special in its own way\, but one stands out among the rest: the S
 antuario de Chimayó\, located in the village of Chimayó. What makes this so
  unique? In one of its side chapels\, there is a hole in the stone floor\, 
 opening onto the sandy earth. Hundreds of thousands of pilgrims\, tourists\
 , and other visitors come to the Santuario every year to gather dirt from t
 his hole\, many believing it has miraculous healing properties. Sometimes c
 alled the “Lourdes of America\,” the Santuario is one of the largest sites 
 of Catholic pilgrimage in North America and a monument to the Hispanic and 
 Catholic origins of much of what is modern United States. In this anecdote-
 rich talk about the Santuario\, Prof. Brett Hendrickson will discuss the va
 rious political and religious regimes that have ruled New Mexico\, examine 
 the meaning of miracles in Hispanic Catholic contexts\, and suggest that ou
 r nation’s origin stories don’t just start on the East Coast but also belon
 g in the U.S.-Mexico borderlands.\n\n \n\nPlease register to attend.
DTEND:20260401T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260315T025454Z
DTSTART:20260401T200000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Religious Studies Speaker Series: Brett Hendrickson
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52249802283958
