BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"First Presbyterian": "https://firstpresevanston.org/event/easter-sunday-worship/", "CitySpark Evanston": "https://firstpresevanston.org/event/easter-sunday-worship/"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"First Presbyterian": "https://firstpresevanston.org/event/easter-sunday-worship/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:first_presbyterian
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston, First Presbyterian
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20260405T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20260405T113000
DTSTAMP:20260314T212905
CREATED:20260225T172635Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260225T172635Z
UID:44645-1775385000-1775388600@firstpresevanston.org
SUMMARY:Easter Sunday Worship
DESCRIPTION:“I have seen the Lord!” — John 20:18 \n\nSunday\, April 5\nWorship at 10:30 a.m.\nFirst Presbyterian Church of Evanston\n1427 Chicago Ave\, Evanston \nExplore all our Easter events\n\nCelebrate the Resurrection with Us\nCome and rejoice with us this Easter Sunday as we celebrate the good news at the heart of our faith: Christ is risen! \nOur Easter worship service is filled with joy\, hope\, and the promise of new life. Whether you’ve been part of First Pres for decades or are visiting for the first time\, you are warmly invited to join us for this celebration of God’s redeeming love. \n\nScripture for the Day\nJohn 20:1–18\nIn this beautiful resurrection story\, we witness: \n\nMary Magdalene discovering the empty tomb at dawn\nPeter and John running to see for themselves\nThe confusion and wonder of those early moments\nMary’s encounter with the risen Jesus\, whom she mistakes for the gardener\nJesus calling her by name — and her joyful response:\n“I have seen the Lord!”\n\nThis passage invites us to discover the hope\, renewal\, and life Jesus offers to each one of us. \n\nWhat to Expect in Worship\nOur Easter service includes: \n\nJoyful\, celebratory music\nScripture reading from John 20:1–18\nA Christ‑centered Easter sermon\nPrayers of thanksgiving\nA welcoming space for families and guests\nA joyful\, hope‑filled atmosphere celebrating the resurrection\n\n\nFamilies & Kids\nChildren are warmly invited to worship with us on Easter morning. \nThere will be a joyful Easter egg hunt and a special photo backdrop for families to capture the day.\n\nParking & Accessibility\n\nParking lot next to the church\nAdditional street parking nearby\nAccessible entrances\nLivestream https://live.firstpresevanston.org/\n\n\nAll Are Welcome\nEaster is the perfect time to explore faith\, reconnect with a church family\, or simply receive the hope God offers. We would be delighted to celebrate with you.
URL:https://firstpresevanston.org/event/easter-sunday-worship/
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Evanston\, 1427 Chicago Avenue Evanston\, IL\, 60201\, United States
CATEGORIES:Featured Event
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://firstpresevanston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/easterSundayResurrection-800-x-600.jpg
END:VEVENT
