DESCRIPTION:Explore composting and learn how to try it at home. We’ll als
 o talk about trash and garbage and where it all ends up. Then test your kn
 owledge with a hands-on sorting game.Part presentation\, part discussion\,
  and part hands-on activity\, the Climate Optimism in Action series gives 
 you the opportunity to learn and explore how to engage with the environmen
 t in a positive way. Each session will be action-based\, exploring a seaso
 nal topic that gives you information and steps to become a climate optimis
 t. Discussions will be led by Angela Stenberg of The Talking Farm. Teen p
 articipants will earn service hours. Fill out this contact form to be adde
 d to the library's list of interested teen volunteers and be one of the fi
 rst to know about volunteer opportunities.Email the teen team if you have 
 any questions.Keyword: Teen Volunteering
