BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Cityspark Evanston": "https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=5#/details/talks-ehc-writing-and-re-writing-home-evanston-in-memoir/18234263/2026-04-12T16"}
X-SOURCE-ID:cityspark_evanston
SUMMARY:Talks@EHC: Writing  and Re-writing Home: Evanston in Memoir
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260412T163000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260412T180000
UID:260302RhU2g0qFOkKzRe2mNpxi6w
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/q_lLO5Pcd0i0UOHqxwhW7Q.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:How do we remember our own past? How do we use language to exp
 lore our own relationship to places that are important to us? Join Evansto
 n writers Joanne Jacobson and Ann Hudson for a discussion of how Jacobson
 ’s trilogy of memoirs recall Evanston landmarks like the B&G diner\, the
  Evanshire Pharmacy\, and Lee Street Beach: their cheeseburgers and cherry
  Cokes\, perfume samplers and roasted nuts\, their textures of sand and su
 n. And we’ll explore how remembering and writing about Evanston—or any
  home—evolves and changes over one writer’s lifetime: how “memory”
  itself is written and re-written. FREE\; RSVP recommended.\n\nPart of Hom
 e: Evanston\, an exploration of what it means to make a home\, and feel at
  home\, in Evanston.
LOCATION:Evanston History Center
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/talks-ehc-writing-and-re-writing-home-evanston-in-memoir/182342
 63/2026-04-12T16
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
