BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern Community": "https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/639969"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern_community
SUMMARY:SESP Teaching\, Learning\, and Education Program Open House
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260415T193000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260415T213000Z
UID:c6c1cf7e1a6ae7b9de0873de782aa7cc@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:This Open House event is for Northwestern undergraduate studen
 ts or staff who are interested in a career in education. There will be var
 ious stations set up where students can learn more about our program and e
 ngage with TLEP faculty and staff.  We are excited to learn about student
 s' interests while considering how our programs can help them reach their 
 goals.  \nThe Teaching\, Learning\, and Education Program has a variety o
 f pathways that can support candidates in becoming a transformative educat
 or. Our program is designed for students who aspire to be a classroom teac
 her or an educator in other spaces\, or who wish to study learning\, explo
 re important issues in education\, or learn more about the design of learn
 ing environments. Our undergraduate programs include SESP Elementary Teach
 ing\, SESP Secondary Teaching\, and pathways to completing teacher licensu
 re requirements while enrolled in a school other than SESP. Additionally\,
  we offer the traditional Master of Science in Education & Social Policy w
 ith concentrations in Classroom Teaching (Elementary\, Secondary)\, Educat
 ional Studies\, and Learning Sciences. Finally\, we offer the Accelerated 
 Master of Science in Education & Social Policy\, in which students may obt
 ain a bachelor’s and master's degree in as little as 5 years by completi
 ng some coursework towards any of the MSED concentrations during their und
 ergraduate studies.\nDrop-ins are welcome!  If students know in advance t
 hey would like to attend\, they can complete this RSVP. Feel free to drop 
 by and play games! Popcorn will be provided. \n *Please note that the fi
 nal admission application deadline for the Master of Science in Education 
 & Social Policy Program for a Fall 2026 entry is July 10th\, 2026.
LOCATION:Norris University Center\, 1999 Campus Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/639969
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
