X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eisenhower Library": "https://eisenhower.librarycalendar.com/event/cristina-henriquez-12809", "Morton Grove Library": "https://www.mgpl.org/event/copy-beyond-page-percival-everett-online-63521", "Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/cristina-henriquez-voice-culture-and-human-connection-14097"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eisenhower Library": "https://eisenhower.librarycalendar.com/event/cristina-henriquez-12809"}
X-SOURCE-ID:eisenhower_library
X-SOURCE:Eisenhower Library, Morton Grove Library, Skokie Library
UID:12809
DTSTAMP:20260315T025613Z
SUMMARY:Cristina Henríquez: Voice\, Culture\, and Human Connection
URL;VALUE=URI:https://eisenhower.librarycalendar.com/event/cristina-henriqu
 ez-12809
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20250710T022846Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260225T224228Z
DESCRIPTION:Join critically acclaimed\, bestselling author\, Cristina Henr
 íquez on Zoom for a compelling conversation about her work. Henríquez’
 s newest book\, The Great Divide\, is a moving exploration of the people 
 who lived\, loved\, and labored during the construction of the Panama Cana
 l. Named a New York Times’ Editors’ Choice selection and TIME Magaz
 ine “100 Must-Read Books of 2024\,” The Great Divide explores histor
 y and adversity in a place very special to her – her father’s homelan
 d of Panama.Henríquez has also authored The Book of Unknown Americans\,
  The World in Half\, and Come Together\, Fall Apart\, all to significant
  acclaim. Her fiction has appeared in The New Yorker\, The Atlantic\, The
  New York Times\, and The Best American Short Stories 2018\, and she is a 
 recipient of the 21st Century Award given by The Chicago Public Library Fo
 undation. She is a graduate of Northwestern University and the Iowa Write
 r’s Workshop\, and lives in the Chicago suburbs with her family.Carmen 
 Álvarez will join Henríquez as moderator. Álvarez is an advocate for li
 braries and Latinx representation in the publishing industry. Her work has
  appeared in Glamour\, Elle\, and Vogue and she has a social media presen
 ce surpassing 180k followers across platforms.Save Your Zoom Seats
CATEGORIES:Conversations
DTSTART:20260417T000000Z
DTEND:20260417T010000Z
LOCATION:US
ROOM:Virtual
IMAGE;ALTREP="Cristina Henríquez: Voice, Culture, and Human Connection";DI
 SPLAY=FULLSIZE;VALUE=URI:https://eisenhower.librarycalendar.com/sites/defa
 ult/files/2026-02/04-16%20Cristina%20Henr%C3%ADquez%20WEB1.jpg
END:VEVENT
