LAST-MODIFIED:20260302T212849Z
DESCRIPTION:In this online interview\, critically acclaimed\, bestselling a
 uthor\, Cristina Henríquez\, will discuss her work. Henríquez’s newest
  book\, The Great Divide\, is a moving exploration of the people who live
 d\, loved\, and labored during the construction of the Panama Canal. Named
  a New York Times Editors’ Choice selection and TIME Magazine “100 M
 ust-Read Books of 2024\,” The Great Divide explores history and adversit
 y in a place very special to her–her father’s homeland of Panama. Thi
 s program will not be shown in person at the library. Register Here!This 
 is an online event\, made possible by Illinois Libraries Present\, a state
 wide collaboration between public libraries\, including Lincolnwood Public
  Library.
