DESCRIPTION:Downton Abbey: The Grand Finale It’s time to say goodbye. Th
 is is the third movie in the Downton Abbey franchise\, which continues the
  popular TV series. It’s 1930 and the future of Downton Abbey is now in 
 Mary’s hands. However\, the scandal of Mary’s pending divorce results 
 in social disgrace\, and there are those who think a woman in her position
  cannot be head of the prominent Crawley family. Think again. Times are ch
 anging. You’ll love the beautiful scenery\, sets\, costumes\, and chara
 cters who are like old friends. All the storylines come full circle to a v
 ery satisfying conclusion.Starring Hugh Bonneville\, Jim Carter\, Michelle
  Dockery\, Paul Giamatti\, Elizabeth McGovern\, and Penelope Wilton.2025 :
  124 minutes : PG for smoking\, suggestive material and some thematic elem
 ents : DramaFree tickets will be given to those who attend.Watch a trailer
  for Downton Abbey: The Grand Finale.Find Downton Abbey: The Grand Finale
  in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Movie
