X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Cityspark Evanston": "https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=5#/details/live-at-studio5-new-nostalgia/18274792/2026-04-17T19"}
X-SOURCE-ID:cityspark_evanston
SUMMARY:Live at Studio5! New Nostalgia
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T193000
UID:260309S-e8z0dBpU6CHPZoiJ6e1Q
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/4oI1LyGrmkKoy3u_szwe7A.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Extraordinary\, high-octane horn-based fusion band returns to 
 Studio5 to perform selections from their powerful new album\, the eponymou
 sly titled\, “New Nostalgia\,” which just came out in December. This 
 concert will be recorded live for Chicago Jazz Live on WDCB.\n\nStudio5 is
  a performing arts venue that opened in Evanston in 2016\, bringing profes
 sional dance\, music\, and spoken word events to a 128-seat theater. Found
 ed and curated by Dance Center Evanston director Béa Rashid and Emmy-awar
 d winning composer and jazz musician Steve Rashid\, Studio5 provides North
  Shore arts-goers with a venue that is both state-of-the-art and intimate\
 , connecting audiences and artists. Studio5 boasts great sight lines\; com
 fortable seats\; excellent sound\; ample\, free parking\; and a cash bar t
 hat opens half an hour before each performance.
LOCATION:Studio5
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/live-at-studio5-new-nostalgia/18274792/2026-04-17T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Cityspark Evanston": "https://tockify.com/enjoyevanston/detail/673/1776472200000"}
X-SOURCE-ID:cityspark_evanston
SUMMARY:O Jerusalem! Crossroad of Three Faiths
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T213000
UID:251109gP5a1FcqbE2jnZ7rS7F7Fw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/-eq_PTnsNUOJnXczMtcyvw.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Ringing with urgency in our time\, this acclaimed program crea
 ted by Jeannette Sorrell returns in a fresh version. Honoring the peoples 
 whose music and faith brought such vibrancy to the Middle East\, 26 artist
 s from Jewish\, Palestinian\, Muslim\, and Christian backgrounds perfo rm 
 on oud\, theorbo\, medieval harp\, zither\, strings\, and exotic percu ssi
 on.\n\nIn this musical tour of the four quarters of Old Jerusalem \\(Jewis
 h\, Christian\, Arab\, and Armenian\\)\, surprising cross-influences emer 
 ge. A Sephardic ballad leads to a classical Arabic love song\; selections 
 from Monteverdi's great Vespers of 1610 echo the exotic and rapturous sing
 ing of the Jewish cantors in the temples. The rhythms of daily life - love
 \, singing\, dancing and prayer - culminate in a joyous celebration of sha
 red humanity.
LOCATION:Nichols Concert Hall
URL:https://tockify.com/enjoyevanston/detail/673/1776472200000
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
