BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/karen-kan-walsh-and-julian-kwok-piano-0"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Karen Kan-Walsh and Julian Kwok\, piano
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T020000Z
UID:a7fa143b5688e5aeb158b2a8b2f1c618@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Coordinator of keyboard skills and non-major piano at the Bien
 en School\, Karen Kan-Walsh has given performances in Russia and China\, a
 s well as throughout the Chicago and Ann Arbor areas. An active member of 
 the Illinois State Music Teachers Association\, she also served as a revie
 wer for Clavier magazine. Guest collaborative pianist Julian Kwok (‘03 D
 Mus) maintains a private voice studio in New York and holds certificates i
 n vocal and clarinet performance as well as diplomas in piano performance 
 from the Royal Schools of Music\, London. Their program showcases music fo
 r two pianos as well as Bach’s Concerto for Two Pianos in C Minor\, feat
 uring an ensemble conducted by Yelisey (Eli) Zelman.\nSergei Rachmaninoff\
 , Suite No. 2 for Two Pianos\, Op. 17\nManuel Infante\, Danses andalouses\
 nJ. S. Bach\, Concerto for Two Pianos in C Minor\, BWV 1060
LOCATION:Patrick G. and Shirley W. Ryan Center for the Musical Arts\, 70 A
 rts Circle\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/karen-kan-walsh-and-julian-k
 wok-piano-0
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern Community": "https://physics.northwestern.edu/about/dearborn-observatory/index.html"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern_community
SUMMARY:Friday Nights at the Dearborn Observatory
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T020000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260418T040000Z
UID:52c7b0dc07f4dbe14610b549a90dd214@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:The Dearborn Observatory is open for public viewing every Frid
 ay night from 9 to 11 pm during the spring and summer months (Apr-Sept). T
 he sessions are free and open to all. Reservations are required for the fi
 rst hour but walk-ins are welcome in the second hour. All visitors should 
 note that the dome is neither heated nor air-conditioned so please dress a
 ppropriately. Friday evening sessions are held "rain or shine." Unfortunat
 ely\, the Dearborn is NOT ADA-accessible. Several staircases must be climb
 ed in order to reach the telescope.\nTo make a reservation go to http://si
 tes.northwestern.edu/dearborn/.\nFor more information on the Dearborn Obse
 rvatory\, please visit our website.\nIf you have any questions\, please em
 ail Adrienne Mintz at adrienne.mintz@northwestern.edu or call 847-491-3644
 .
LOCATION:Dearborn Observatory\, 2131 Tech Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://physics.northwestern.edu/about/dearborn-observatory/index.html
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
