BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern Community": "https://quantum.northwestern.edu/events/northwestern-quantum-week/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern_community
SUMMARY:Northwestern Quantum Week: Opening Science Workshop on Superconduc
 ting Qubits for Quantum Computing
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T133000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T223000Z
UID:f1890666e548056b4b50de8d8a69aeda@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:The Institute for Quantum Information Research and Engineering
  (INQUIRE) invites you to the Opening Workshop on Superconducting Qubit Te
 chnology for Quantum Computing\, which will take place on April 20 & April
  21\, 2026\, at Northwestern University in Evanston\, IL. \nThe workshop 
 is part of Northwestern Quantum Week\, which is devoted to building connec
 tions between quantum research scientists\, engineers\, industry leaders\,
  alumni\, investors\, and other experts dedicated to quantum discovery\, e
 ducation\, and applied innovation. \nRegistration is now open for the eve
 nt. \nDetails:\nDate: Tuesday\, April 21\nTime: 8:30am-5:30pm (CT)\nLocat
 ion: Guild Lounge\nRSVP: Register here\nThe workshop will feature talks fr
 om the following individuals:\n•   Anna Grassellino\, Fermi National Ac
 celerator Laboratory\n•   Mark Hersam\, Northwestern University\n•  
  Andrew Houk\, Princeton University\n•   Angela Kou\, University of Ill
 inois Urbana-Champaign\n•   Robert McDermott\, University of Wisconsin-
 Madison\n•   William Oliver\, Massachusetts Institute of Technology\n
 •   Johannes Pollanen\, Michigan State University\n•   David Schuste
 r\, Stanford University\nFor more information\, please contact K. Michael 
 Brooks at quantum@northwestern.edu.
LOCATION:Scott Hall\, 601 University Place\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://quantum.northwestern.edu/events/northwestern-quantum-week/
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
