BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern Community": "https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/639896"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern_community
SUMMARY:"AI & The Future of Education" Featuring\, Moderated by Karen Smil
 owitz
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T183000Z
UID:d6a868c31853832b205844afb695e109@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an in-person Distinguished Panel event featuring N
 NCI's new Education Pillar Leads\, ___________ & ____________\, moderated 
 by Karen Smilowitz. \nTitle: "AI & The Future of Education"\nHigher educa
 tion is at an inflection point. As artificial intelligence rapidly reshape
 s how we teach\, learn\, and conduct research\, universities face pressing
  questions about what this means for students\, faculty\, and institutions
  alike.\nThis panel brings together thought leaders from Northwestern to e
 xplore how AI is transforming the higher education landscape — from the 
 classroom to the research lab. Panelists will discuss the opportunities an
 d challenges AI presents for learning outcomes\, academic integrity\, inst
 itutional governance\, and the evolving roles of educators and students. T
 he conversation will also consider how universities can thoughtfully adapt
  to ensure AI serves as a tool for equity and excellence rather than a sou
 rce of new inequities.\nLunch will be provided. Registration is required.
LOCATION:Chambers Hall\, 600 Foster St\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/639896
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern Community": "https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/631493"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern_community
SUMMARY:CCHS lecture by Erika Pani
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T170000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T190000Z
UID:f7715cdc9976720777a69dfee4c27c8a@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Erika PANI (College of Mexico)\, author of Torn Asunder: Repub
 lican Crises and Civil Wars in the United States and Mexico\, 1848–1867 
 (2025)—Tuesday\, April 21— LUNCH LECTURE:\n “Does North America Hav
 e a Common History? The View from the Nineteenth Century"\nThis lecture is
  part of the annual lunch lecture series organized by the Nicholas D. Chab
 raja Center for Historical Studies (CCHS). Catered lunch starts at 12 noon
 \, lecture about 12:30 p.m.
LOCATION:Harris Hall\, 1881 Sheridan Road\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/631493
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
