DESCRIPTION:Small Things Like TheseBased on the book by Claire Keegan. Set 
 in 1985 Christmastime in the Irish Village New Ross\, the story follows co
 al merchant Bill Furlong\, a hardworking father of five daughters. While d
 elivering coal to a local convent\, he witnesses harsh treatment of a youn
 g girl and later\, while making an earlier than usual delivery to the conv
 ent\, he discovers teenaged Sarah locked in the shed. These events lead to
  a flashback to his own difficult childhood\, growing up the son of an unw
 ed mother. What can he do in the present\, especially in a small community
  that is afraid to challenge the status quo? Starring Cillian Murphy\, Ei
 leen Walsh\, and Emily Watson.After watching the film\, share your questio
 ns and comments in a discussion with Chris and Sharon.2024 : 98 minutes : 
 Rated PG-13 for thematic material : Drama.Free tickets will be given to th
 ose who attend.Watch the trailer for Small Things Like These.Find Small Th
 ings Like These in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Movie
