BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/639981"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:The Power of the Pen: Fiction Workshop | Sexual Assault Action Mon
 th
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T000000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T013000Z
UID:c4a696587720dc0a64c8ca66f5aea7a1@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Writing fiction can provide an avenue to process and heal for 
 many survivors of interpersonal violence. Incorporating themes and histori
 es of harm into fictional narratives is a form of creativity and expressio
 n that may allow survivors to grow more resilient and access pathways to h
 ealing. This workshop will explore the ways survivors can use fiction writ
 ing to process their experiences and pursue healing. It will offer insight
 s on how to pull from fact for the purposes of fiction writing and hold sp
 ace for reflection and free writing.  \n \nFood provided | Registration 
 Required
LOCATION:Women's Center\, 2000 Sheridan Rd.\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/639981
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
