BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern Community": "https://quantum.northwestern.edu/events/northwestern-quantum-week/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern_community
SUMMARY:Northwestern Quantum Week: Quantum Innovation Symposium
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T133000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T223000Z
UID:676bbb4e840a46b79bb4881371e343f0@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:The Institute for Quantum Information Research and Engineering
  (INQUIRE) invites you to the Inaugural Quantum Innovation Symposium\, whi
 ch will take place on April 22\, 2026\, at Northwestern University in Evan
 ston\, IL. \nThe symposium is part of Northwestern Quantum Week\, which i
 s devoted to building connections between quantum research scientists\, en
 gineers\, industry leaders\, alumni\, investors\, and other experts dedica
 ted to quantum discovery\, education\, and applied innovation. \nRegistra
 tion is now open for the event. \nThe Quantum Innovation Symposium foster
 s collaborative exchange by bringing together senior scientists\, engineer
 s\, and other quantum innovators\, including Northwestern alumni with lead
 ership roles across quantum industry and research sectors. \nDetails:\nDa
 te: Tuesday\, April 21\nTime: 8:30am-5:30pm (CT)\nLocation: Guild Lounge\n
 RSVP: Register here\nThe symposium will feature talks from the following i
 ndividuals:\n•   Aaron Fluitt\, PsiQuantum\n•   Nikos Hardavellas\
 , Northwestern University\n•   Yuping Huang\, Quantum Computing\, Inc.
 \n•   Heejeong Jeong\, Pasqal\n•   Abhinav Kandala\, IBM Quantum\n
 •   Rejkumar Kettimuthu\, Globus GridFTP\n•   Indermohan S. Monga\
 , Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory\n•   Eric Perreault\, Northwes
 tern University\n•   Juliette Peyronnet\, Alice & Bob\n•   Johanne
 s Pollanen\, EeroQ Quantum Hardware\n•   Laura Schulz\, Argonne Leader
 ship Computing Facility\n•   Kate Smith\, Northwestern University\n•
    Michael Wasielewski\, Northwestern University\nThis is an excellent o
 pportunity to connect\, share ideas\, and foster collaborations within the
  quantum science community. \nFor more information\, contact quantum@nort
 hwestern.edu.
LOCATION:Scott Hall\, 601 University Place\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://quantum.northwestern.edu/events/northwestern-quantum-week/
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
