BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern Community": "https://quantum.northwestern.edu/cmqt/events/symposium/2026-symposium/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern_community
SUMMARY:Northwestern Quantum Week: CMQT Symposium - Keynote Speaker
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T223000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T233000Z
UID:82c3653f329c2915927d06e827b1e219@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:On behalf of the Institute for Quantum Information Research an
 d Engineering (INQUIRE)\, we are delighted to welcome you to the Fifth Ann
 ual Symposium of the Center for Molecular Quantum Transduction (CMQT)\, a 
 US DOE-sponsored Energy Frontier Research Center\, which will take place o
 n April 23 & 24\, 2026\, in Evanston\, IL.\nThe symposium is part of North
 western Quantum Week\, which is devoted to building connections between qu
 antum research scientists\, engineers\, industry leaders\, alumni\, invest
 ors\, and other experts dedicated to quantum discovery\, education\, and a
 pplied innovation. \nRegistration is now open for the event.\nThis sympos
 ium is an annual event that enhances communication and collaboration betwe
 en member research institutions and personnel as well as the broader quant
 um information community to generate research ideas and accelerate innovat
 ion.\nDetails:\nDate: Thursday\, April 23\nTime: 5:30pm-6:30pm (CT)\nLocat
 ion: Pancoe Auditorium\nRSVP: Register here\nThe symposium will feature ta
 lks from the following individuals:\n•   Dmitri Basov\, Columbia Unive
 rsity [keynote speaker]\n•   Claudia Avalos\, New York University\n•
    Justin Caram\, University of California\, Los Angeles\n•   Gregor
 y Fuchs\, Cornell University\n•   Ryan Hadt\, California Institute of 
 Technology\n•   Martin Holt\, Argonne National Laboratory\n•   Mar
 tin Kirk\, University of New Mexico\nThis is an excellent opportunity to c
 onnect\, share ideas\, and foster collaborations within the quantum scienc
 e community.\nFor more information\, contact Keller Paulson at quantum@nor
 thwestern.edu.
LOCATION:Pancoe-NSUHS Life Sciences Pavilion\, 2200 Campus Drive\, Evansto
 n\, IL
URL:https://quantum.northwestern.edu/cmqt/events/symposium/2026-symposium/
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
