BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Cityspark Evanston": "https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=5#/details/petra-van-nuis-dennis-luxion-quintet/18310981/2026-04-24T19"}
X-SOURCE-ID:cityspark_evanston
SUMMARY:Petra van Nuis & Dennis Luxion Quintet
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260424T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260424T193000
UID:260311eYOyFvQxKUe_fJUs57RMjw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/a_6JaeIrVkqYsUdEzhttCg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Legendary trumpeter/vocalist Chet Baker was revered for being 
 a centerpiece of the cool jazz sounds in the 1950s. In this show\, entitle
 d “Remembering Chet — Songs & Stories of Chet Baker\,” well-known Ch
 icago vocalist Petra van Nuis will team up with Baker’s former pianist D
 ennis Luxion to share personal stories and perform Baker’s iconic music.
  This concert will be recorded live for Chicago Jazz Live on WDCB.\n\nStud
 io5 is a performing arts venue that opened in Evanston in 2016\, bringing 
 professional dance\, music\, and spoken word events to a 128-seat theater.
  Founded and curated by Dance Center Evanston director Béa Rashid and Emm
 y-award winning composer and jazz musician Steve Rashid\, Studio5 provides
  North Shore arts-goers with a venue that is both state-of-the-art and int
 imate\, connecting audiences and artists. Studio5 boasts great sight lines
 \; comfortable seats\; excellent sound\; ample\, free parking\; and a cash
  bar that opens half an hour before each performance.
LOCATION:Studio5 Performing Arts Center
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/petra-van-nuis-dennis-luxion-quintet/18310981/2026-04-24T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
