SUMMARY:Civic Love
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/civic-love-16986
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251210T153600Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251229T205805Z
DESCRIPTION:Outside in our south courtyard with cozy fire vibes\, see how c
 ivic love appears in your life and how you can strengthen relationships in
  your community.36 Questions for Civic Love is a tool created by the Natio
 nal Public Housing Museum (NPHM)\, based on psychologist Arthur Aron and D
 etroit-based organizer Grace Lee Boggs’ work. According to the NPHM\, 
 “Civic love is one’s love for society\, expressed through a commitment
  to the common good. It is a belief in the idea that we’re all better of
 f\, when we are all better off." In this event\, you will connect with fri
 ends and neighbors and learn how you can experience and grow the practice 
 of civic love. Keyword: USA 250
CATEGORIES:Civic Engagement,Social Gathering
DTSTART:20260427T230000Z
DTEND:20260428T000000Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:South Courtyard
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
