SUMMARY:Jazz Small Ensembles: The Music of Miles Davis
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T010000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T023000Z
UID:35991bb1302224129be16bb0b2b9cba5@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Derrick Gardner and Kevin Fort\, conductors\nThe Derrick Gardn
 er and Kevin Fort ensembles continue the celebration of the Miles Davis ce
 ntennial with a selection of the legendary trumpeter\, bandleader\, and co
 mposer’s boundary-pushing compositions. Over the course of a career span
 ning nearly five decades\, Davis remained at the vanguard of multiple styl
 istic developments in jazz\, including bebop\, cool jazz\, hard bop\, moda
 l jazz\, and fusion.
LOCATION:Patrick G. and Shirley W. Ryan Center for the Musical Arts\, 70 A
 rts Circle\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/jazz-small-ensembles-20
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
