BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/love-and-information/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Love & Information
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T003000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T021500Z
UID:4584d19ae4054a85beebd8fbc5fdce80@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:By Caryl Churchill\nDirected by Claire Bauman \nSomeone sneez
 es. Someone can’t get a signal. Someone won’t answer the door. Someone
  put an elephant on the stairs. Someone’s not ready to talk. Someone is 
 her brother’s mother. Someone hates irrational numbers. Someone told the
  police. Someone got a message from the traffic light. Someone’s never f
 elt like this before.\nIn this fast-moving kaleidoscope\, more than a hund
 red characters try to make sense of what they know.\nApproximate run time:
  1 hour and 45 minutes\, no intermission\nSuggested Ages: 13+
LOCATION:Wirtz Center: Ethel M. Barber Theater\, 30 Arts Circle Drive\, Ev
 anston\, IL
URL:https://wirtz.northwestern.edu/love-and-information/
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern Community": "https://physics.northwestern.edu/about/dearborn-observatory/index.html"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern_community
SUMMARY:Friday Nights at the Dearborn Observatory
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T020000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T040000Z
UID:d8495ee427812cf2b5aa377266ff1af2@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:The Dearborn Observatory is open for public viewing every Frid
 ay night from 9 to 11 pm during the spring and summer months (Apr-Sept). T
 he sessions are free and open to all. Reservations are required for the fi
 rst hour but walk-ins are welcome in the second hour. All visitors should 
 note that the dome is neither heated nor air-conditioned so please dress a
 ppropriately. Friday evening sessions are held "rain or shine." Unfortunat
 ely\, the Dearborn is NOT ADA-accessible. Several staircases must be climb
 ed in order to reach the telescope.\nTo make a reservation go to http://si
 tes.northwestern.edu/dearborn/.\nFor more information on the Dearborn Obse
 rvatory\, please visit our website.\nIf you have any questions\, please em
 ail Adrienne Mintz at adrienne.mintz@northwestern.edu or call 847-491-3644
 .
LOCATION:Dearborn Observatory\, 2131 Tech Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://physics.northwestern.edu/about/dearborn-observatory/index.html
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University (Community)
END:VEVENT
