X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Winnetka Northfield Library": "https://www.wnpld.org/event/americas-oddest-museums-37099"}
X-SOURCE-ID:winnetka_northfield_library
X-SOURCE:Winnetka Northfield Library
UID:37099
DTSTAMP:20260315T025452Z
SUMMARY:America's Oddest Museums - Film Screening
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.wnpld.org/event/americas-oddest-museums-37099
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251203T224205Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260211T161605Z
DESCRIPTION:Join multi-Emmy Award winning producer and editor Harvey Moshma
 n for a screening of a 1-hour special of the PBS series Wild Travels. When
  it comes to museums\, there’s the kind your school made you go to on fi
 eld trips\, but what about the quirkier variety that feature collections o
 f mustard\, or pinball machines\, or even just dust\; that showcase action
  figures\, or portraits made entirely from bugs? The kind of museums that 
 are located in motel lobbies\, or in homemade castles\, or abandoned barns
 ? Learn about them all in AMERICA'S ODDEST MUSEUMS. Screening followed by 
 live Q&A.
CATEGORIES:History,Other
DTSTART:20260503T190000Z
DTEND:20260503T203000Z
LOCATION:768 Oak Street\, Winnetka\, IL\, 60093\, US
ROOM:Lloyd Room
GEO:42.1043086;-87.732896
IMAGE;ALTREP=wild travels;DISPLAY=FULLSIZE;VALUE=URI:https://www.wnpld.org/
 sites/default/files/2026-01/WT%20POSTER%20Horiz_0.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Northwestern": "https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/symphonic-band-9"}
X-SOURCE-ID:northwestern
SUMMARY:Symphonic Band
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260503T200000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260503T213000Z
UID:d008890a15d4e5b75ff7dc1a2ba409e5@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Shawn Vondran\, conductor\nThe centerpiece of the Symphonic Ba
 nd’s first spring concert is Modest Mussorgsky’s Pictures at an Exhibi
 tion (orchestrated by Maurice Ravel and transcribed for band by Paul Laven
 der). The pictures the work depicts were created by Mussorgsky’s friend\
 , artist Viktor Hartmann. Following Hartmann’s untimely death\, the Impe
 rial Academy of Arts in Saint Petersburg exhibited his work\, and after to
 uring the exhibition\, Mussorgsky was inspired to compose the score.\nJoha
 n Halvorsen (arr. Frederick Fennell)\, Bojarernes intogsmarsch (Entry Marc
 h of the Boyars) \nEric Whitacre\, Lux Aurumque \nDennis Llinás\, La Ch
 ancla \nModest Mussorgsky (orch. Maurice Ravel\, trans. Paul Lavender)\, 
 Pictures at an Exhibition
LOCATION:Pick-Staiger Concert Hall\, 50 Arts Circle Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/symphonic-band-9
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
