X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:23933
DTSTAMP:20260315T025448Z
SUMMARY:Morning Movie
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/morning-movie-23933
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260204T023732Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T172955Z
DESCRIPTION:Elio Eleven-year-old Elio believes that extraterrestrials are 
 out there and feels he’d fit in better with them. One day\, his dream co
 mes true: he's taken to the Communiverse and is mistaken for an ambassador
  from Earth. This fun\, action-packed cosmic misadventure explores themes 
 of loneliness\, belonging\, grief\, loss\, family\, acceptance\, self-disc
 overy\, and identity. Elio and his space-alien best friend Glordon are end
 earing and relatable\, and the animation is bright and imaginative. Featu
 ring the voice talents of Yonas Kibreab\, Remy Edgerly\, Zoe Saldana\, Bra
 d Garrett\, Jameela Jamil\, Shirley Henderson\, and Matthias Schweighofer.
  Directed by Madeline Sharafian\, Domee Shi\, and Adrian Molina. This rece
 ived an Oscar nomination for Best Animated Feature Film. 2025 : 98 minute
 s : Rated PG for some action/peril and thematic elements : AnimationFree t
 ickets will be given to all who attend. Watch the trailer for Elio.Find E
 lio in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Movie
DTSTART:20260504T150000Z
DTEND:20260504T164500Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Petty Auditorium
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
