DESCRIPTION:Two women find that they have everything in common until the d
 eath of a brother drives them apart. Part stand-up comedy\, part stand-up 
 tragedy for two. The redhaired mythology that glorifies and empowers two w
 omen leads them into a big love\, but can’t lead them safely out again. 
 A play about the heaviness of the things we carry. Approximate run time: 1
  hour and 40 minutes\, with one intermission. Suggested ages: 16\\+
LOCATION:Wirtz Center for the Performing Arts Hal & Martha Hyer Wallis The
 ater
