BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/own-interview-preparation-reduces-interview-anxiety-22858"}
X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:22858
DTSTAMP:20260315T025448Z
SUMMARY:Own the Interview: Preparation That Reduces Anxiety
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/own-interview-preparatio
 n-reduces-interview-anxiety-22858
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260127T213526Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260309T212010Z
DESCRIPTION:Interviews feel uncertain\, and uncertainty creates anxiety. Th
 is workshop shows how focused preparation reduces both. You’ll build a s
 tory vault of accomplishments to make your value clear\; create confident 
 first lines with powerful\, intentional language\; and sketch a simple 90-
 day plan that signals your readiness. You'll learn to apply powerful\, in
 tentional language so that you start your answers with confidence and how 
 to implement a simple system with a workbook to stay consistent and in co
 ntrol.Presented on Zoom in partnership with the Lake Cook Career Collabora
 tive. The presentation will be recorded and available for viewing afterwar
 d. Register and receive a Zoom link.
DTSTART:20260519T233000Z
DTEND:20260520T010000Z
LOCATION:US
ROOM:Online
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eisenhower Library": "https://eisenhower.librarycalendar.com/event/rebecca-f-kuang-12767", "Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/babel-rf-kuang-24985"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eisenhower Library": "https://eisenhower.librarycalendar.com/event/rebecca-f-kuang-12767"}
X-SOURCE-ID:eisenhower_library
X-SOURCE:Eisenhower Library, Skokie Library
UID:12767
DTSTAMP:20260315T025614Z
SUMMARY:Babel-On with R.F. Kuang
URL;VALUE=URI:https://eisenhower.librarycalendar.com/event/rebecca-f-kuang-
 12767
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20250704T220212Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260226T165619Z
DESCRIPTION:R.F. Kuang’s genre-bending fiction broaches ordinarily seriou
 s topics from a satirical and fantastical perspective. Academic yet approa
 chable\, Kuang’s work combines history\, magic\, and classical literary 
 tradition to render powerful critiques of academia\, the publishing indust
 ry\, and even contemporary popular culture. Her most recent novel\, Kata
 basis\, follows two graduate students as they descend into hell after the 
 death of their professor\, and the screen rights options to the novel were
  sold to Amazon MGM Studios for an upcoming TV series before its publicati
 on. Kuang’s other bestselling titles include Yellowface\, Babel\, and
  The Poppy War trilogy\, and she is the recipient of the Nebula Award fo
 r Best Novel\, the Goodreads Choice Awards for Best Fiction\, and the Amer
 ican Book Award. Kelly Jensen\, an anti-censorship advocate\, a senior ed
 itor at Book Riot\, and writer who has compiled such anthologies as Here W
 e Are: Feminism for the Real World and (Don’t) Call Me Crazy\, will be 
 joining Kuang in conversation.Save Your Zoom Seats
CATEGORIES:Conversations
DTSTART:20260520T000000Z
DTEND:20260520T010000Z
LOCATION:US
ROOM:Virtual
IMAGE;ALTREP=Babel-On with Author R.F. Kuang;DISPLAY=FULLSIZE;VALUE=URI:htt
 ps://eisenhower.librarycalendar.com/sites/default/files/2026-02/05-19%20R.
 F.%20Kuang%20WEB1.jpg
END:VEVENT
