BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Morton Grove Library": "https://www.mgpl.org/event/between-lines-mighty-red-louise-erdrich-online-63546"}
X-SOURCE-ID:morton_grove_library
X-SOURCE:Morton Grove Library
UID:63546
DTSTAMP:20260315T025450Z
SUMMARY:Between the Lines: The Mighty Red by Louise Erdrich (Online)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.mgpl.org/event/between-lines-mighty-red-louise-er
 drich-online-63546
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251121T205220Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T174612Z
DESCRIPTION:Between the Lines meets for online discussions via Zoom. Regist
 ered patrons will receive an email the day before the program with the mee
 ting ID and password for joining the event. New members are warmly welcome
 !Titles are always available on Hoopla\, as well as other library ebook pl
 atforms. Contact us for assistance\, or find any instructions you may need
  on our Download & Stream page.Book Synopsis: In this stunning novel\, Pu
 litzer Prize and National Book Award–winning author Louise Erdrich tells
  a story of love\, natural forces\, spiritual yearnings\, and the tragic i
 mpact of uncontrollable circumstances on ordinary people’s lives.In the 
 Red River Valley of North Dakota\, several lives revolve around a wedding 
 fraught with desire\, jealousy\, and uncertainty. Gary Geist\, a terrified
  young man set to inherit two farms\, is desperate to marry Kismet Poe\, a
 n impulsive\, lapsed goth who can’t read her own future but will settle 
 for fulfilling his. Her best friend\, Hugo\, a gentle\, red-haired\, homes
 chooled giant\, also loves Kismet and is determined to steal her away and 
 build a life together. Kismet’s mother\, Crystal\, drives a truck for Ga
 ry’s family\, and on her nightly runs\, tunes in to the darkness of late
 -night radio\, experiences visions of guardian angels\, and worries about 
 what’s to come\, for her daughter and herself.The Mighty Red is Louise E
 rdrich at her consummate best. A novel of tender humor\, disquietude\, yea
 rning\, community\, and family\, it is about ordinary people who dream\, g
 row up\, fall in love\, struggle\, endure tragedy\, carry bitter secrets\;
  men and women both complicated and contradictory\, flawed and decent\, l
 onely and hopeful. Human time\, deep time\, Red River time\, and geologica
 l time are explored alongside the impact of crises in our own time—clima
 te change\, the depletion of natural resources\, the economic meltdown of 
 2008. It is a story about our tattered bond with the earth\, and about lov
 e in all of its absurdity and splendor.
CATEGORIES:Books & Authors
CONTACT:Adult Services\, info@mgpl.org\, 8479654220
DTSTART:20260527T000000Z
DTEND:20260527T010000Z
LOCATION:US
ROOM:Online
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/fantasy-book-club-22459"}
X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:22459
DTSTAMP:20260315T025448Z
SUMMARY:Fantasy Book Club
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/fantasy-book-club-22459
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260124T233021Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T173117Z
DESCRIPTION:This month we'll be discussing Daughter of the Moon Goddess by 
 Sue Lynn Tan. Growing up on the moon\, Xingyin is unaware that her mother
  is hiding her from the Celestial Emperor. When her magic makes itself kno
 wn\, her existence is discovered and she is forced to run away. While flee
 ing\, she meets the Crown Prince\, who invites her to train alongside him 
 in archery and magic.This fantasy book is inspired by the legend of the Ch
 inese moon goddess\, Chang'e\, and is the first in the Celestial Kingdom d
 uology.Find Daughter of the Moon Goddess in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Books and Authors,Discussion
DTSTART:20260527T000000Z
