BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Skokie Library": "https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/pages-through-history-second-founding-23852"}
X-SOURCE-ID:skokie_library
X-SOURCE:Skokie Library
UID:23852
DTSTAMP:20260315T025448Z
SUMMARY:Pages Through History
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/pages-through-history-se
 cond-founding-23852
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260203T205202Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T173156Z
DESCRIPTION:This month we'll be discussing The Second Founding: How the Civ
 il War and Reconstruction Remade the Constitution by Eric Foner. It would
  be hard for a person contemplating the United States of 1865 not to conc
 lude that the system the Founders had bequeathed the nation just under a c
 entury earlier had been catastrophically flawed. Pulitzer Prize-winning hi
 storian Eric Foner lays out the ways the 13th\, 14th\, and 15th Amendments
 –all passed in just five years–represented an attempt to fix those fla
 ws. They abolished slavery\, codified the principles of birthright citizen
 ship and legal equality\, and guaranteed the right of Black men to vote. W
 e live in the America the “Reconstruction Amendments” made\, but we’
 ve been fighting about those amendments ever since.   Find The Second Fo
 unding in the library catalog.
CATEGORIES:Books and Authors,Civic Engagement
DTSTART:20260528T000000Z
DTEND:20260528T013000Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Cosmos Room
GEO:42.0258969;-87.7580355
END:VEVENT
