DESCRIPTION:Monarch butterflies play an important role as pollinators\, and
  their populations are in trouble. Teen volunteers will learn about them a
 nd teach others\, too.Tend our native garden patch\, observe monarch eggs 
 and caterpillars\, and talk with other library patrons about your observat
 ions and how we can all support monarchs. Data will be submitted to the Mo
 narch Larva Monitoring Project. All participants receive service hours as
  part of Teen Summer Service. All participants receive service hours as pa
 rt of Teen Summer Service. Fill out this contact form to be added to our l
 ist of interested teen volunteers and be one of the first to know about vo
 lunteer opportunities.Email the teen team to learn more or to express an i
 nterest in volunteering. For grade 6-12.
CATEGORIES:Science and STEAM
