DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 45 Miles\n\nLe
 ader: Neal Ney\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https:
 //ridewithgps.com/routes/27865884\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Midd
 leforkSavanna.jpgA savanna is open woodland with grasses and forbs growing
  under the trees. We will ride at a moderate pace to this rare remnant fro
 m Illinois' pre-settlement past. We'll ride a bit more than four miles on 
 the limestone trail in the preserve at a slow pace with some stops for nat
 ure gawking. The trail is suitable for road bikes (as long as you are not 
 in a hurry). After lunch at the Panera on 176\, we will resume our moderat
 e pace on the roads and paved paths back to Evanston.\n\n
LOCATION:Panera Wilmette
