 Sharon Kaminecki)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: Approx 20 mile
 s\n\nLeader: Sharon Kaminecki\n\n## Monthly Moderate Breakfast Club Ride:\
 n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Mucho%20Gusto%20Barra%20%2B%20Concina.
 jpg: https://ridewithgps.com/routes/27045735If you like to eat\, ride a bi
 ke\, meet new people\, explore different parts of the city but dedicate on
 ly half a day doing it at a time\, this service of group bicycle rides is 
 for you! The “Breakfast Club” will ride at a moderate pace to a differ
 ent neighborhood stop for breakfast at a pre-selected restaurant\, and be 
 back around noon.\n\nJoin us as we amigos roll to breakfast at [](https://
 joedonut.com/locations/niles/)**Mucho Gusto Barra + Concina**\, 2700 N Mil
 waukee Ave\, Chicago\, in the Logan Square neighborhood. Inspired by the c
 olors and charm of San Miquel de Allende\, the brunch menu includes breakf
 ast burritos\, chilaquiles\, French toast\, and huevos al bajio.\n\n
LOCATION:Panera\, Wilmette
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
