BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Evanston Bike Club": "https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/D5CB3ACE-D71C-4FB6-A5F9-5607FE8675EF_1_201_a.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Foley%20Pond%20HP.jpg:"}
X-SOURCE-ID:evanston_bike_club
X-SOURCE:Evanston Bike Club
URL:https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/D5CB3ACE-D71C-4FB6-A5F9-5607FE8675EF_1_201_a.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Foley%20Pond%20HP.jpg:
UID:TU2023025283
DTSTAMP:20260315T011111Z
SUMMARY:Foley Pond (Neal Ney)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 30 miles\n\nLe
 ader: Neal Ney\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/D5CB3ACE-D71C-4FB6-A5F9
 -5607FE8675EF_1_201_a.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png!
 https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Foley%20Pond%20HP.jpg: https://ridewithgps
 .com/routes/44025534Tuesday's Moderate Ride: Foley Pond is a hidden gem of
  a park – essentially a fishing hole – in Highland Park. Most of us wo
 uld never stumble across it in our usual comings and goings. It’s hard e
 nough to find when you know that it is there. No parking lot\, very subtle
  signage\, no playground equipment\, and no paved surfaces.\n\nWe’ll rid
 e to Lake Forest along Ridge\, take Old Elm and a few other streets east a
 nd south to Highland Park\, stopping to lunch at Once Upon a Bagel. In par
 t this route is an excuse to visit this old EBC favorite and Stanley-appro
 ved restaurant\, that I don’t think we have visited enough lately. After
  lunch we’ll pay a short visit to Foley Pond. Fishing and birding are th
 e major activities here\, but we won’t be doing either. Just looking and
  maybe taking a couple of pictures.\n\n
LOCATION:Panera\, Wilmette
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph),.Weekly > ...Moderate Wkly
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
