 aron Kaminecki)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: Approx 20 mile
 s\n\nLeader: Sharon Kaminecki\n\n## Monthly Moderate Breakfast Club Ride:\
 n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/The%20Perch%20Kitchen%20and%20Tap.jpg:
  https://ridewithgps.com/routes/27045735If you like to eat\, ride a bike\,
  meet new people\, explore different parts of the city but dedicate only h
 alf a day doing it at a time\, this service of group bicycle rides is for 
 you! The “Breakfast Club” will ride at a moderate pace to a different 
 neighborhood stop for breakfast at a pre-selected restaurant\, and be back
  around noon.\n\nJoin us as we ride to breakfast at **The Perch Kitchen an
 d Tap**\, 1932 W Division\, Chicago in the Wicker Park neighborhood. The b
 runch menu includes omelets\, fried egg sandwich\, avocado toast\, and lem
 on blueberry pancakes.\n\n
