UID:TU2023025343
DTSTAMP:20260315T011111Z
SUMMARY:Middlefork Savanna (Neal Ney)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: 45 Miles\n\nLe
 ader: Neal Ney\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https:
 //ridewithgps.com/routes/27865884\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Midd
 leforkSavanna.jpgThis week's Tuesday Moderate Ride: A savanna is open wood
 land with grasses and forbs growing under the trees. We will ride at a mod
 erate pace to this rare remnant from Illinois' pre-settlement past. We'll 
 ride a bit more than four miles on the limestone trail in the preserve at 
 a slow pace with some stops for nature gawking. The trail is suitable for 
 road bikes (as long as you are not in a hurry). After lunch at the Panera 
 on 176 we will resume our moderate pace on the roads and paved paths back 
 to Evanston.\n\n
LOCATION:Panera\, Wilmette
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph),.Weekly > ...Moderate Wkly
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
