SUMMARY:Corned Beef\, Latkes and Hot Fudge Sundaes on Sunday (Alvin Spector
 )
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Fast\n\nDistance: ~ 40 Miles\n\nLead
 er: Alvin Spector\n\n## !https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Corned%20Beef%20S
 andwich.jpgCorned Beef\, Latkes and Hot Fudge Sundaes on a Sunday\n\n!http
 s://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https://ridewithgps.com/route
 s/46435755Please come on out for a classic Fast (15-17 mph) ride to the fa
 mous Manny’s Deli just off Roosevelt Road and Jefferson south of the Loo
 p. A favorite of Chicago politicians as well as the general public\, Manny
 ’s is an institution of deli delights including one of the best corned b
 eef sandwiches and potato pancakes\, anywhere. Founded in 1942\, this is a
  family run institution where everything\, including the corned beef is ho
 memade. After lunch\, we will ride to Margie’s Candies on Western Avenue
 . A Chicago landmark for over a century\, this old fashioned candy store a
 nd ice cream parlor will provide the perfect dessert for the ride back to 
 Wilmette. Total distance approximately 40 miles.\n\n
LOCATION:Panera\, Wilmette
CATEGORIES:.Fast (15-17 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
