 )
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Moderate\n\nDistance: Approx 20 mile
 s\n\nLeader: Sharon Kaminecki\n\n## Monthly Moderate Breakfast Club Ride:\
 n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Nubar%20Caf%C3%A9.jpg: https://ridewit
 hgps.com/routes/27045735If you like to eat\, ride a bike\, meet new people
 \, explore different parts of the city but dedicate only half a day doing 
 it at a time\, this service of group bicycle rides is for you! The “Brea
 kfast Club” will ride at a moderate pace to a different neighborhood sto
 p for breakfast at a pre-selected restaurant\, and be back around noon.\n\
 nJoin us as we ride to breakfast at **Nubar Café**\, 3200 W Lawrence Ave\
 , a Kurdish café located in the Albany Park neighborhood. We will sample 
 middle eastern and mediterranean breakfast sandwiches\, pastries plus spec
 ialty teas and coffees.\n\n
LOCATION:Panera\, Wilmette
CATEGORIES:..Moderate (13-15 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
