SUMMARY:Barrington Moretti's (Jeff Miller)
DESCRIPTION:Status: Confirmed\n\nPace: Fast\n\nDistance: 58 Miles\n\nLeader
 : Jeff Miller\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https:/
 /ridewithgps.com/routes/39695420\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Barri
 ngton%20Hills.jpgStart: Village Green Park in Northbrook (corner of Walter
 s &amp\; Meadow) at 9 am. If you drive to the start\, the streets may have
  parking restrictions if there is a festival in the park. There is a parki
 ng lot on Walters just southeast of the park where you should be able to p
 ark.\n\nWe will ride through Long Grove and the rolling hills of Barringto
 n Hills\, passing horse farms and mansions. Then our route drops down to o
 ur lunch stop at the Moretti's in Barrington. After lunch we return on bea
 utiful Old Checker Road before stopping at Culver's for a quick rest/snack
 . The pace will be Fast (15-17 mph).\n\n
LOCATION:Village Green\, Northbrook
CATEGORIES:.Fast (15-17 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
