SUMMARY:Skokie Holiday Lights Ride (David Barish)
DESCRIPTION:Status: PENDING!\n\nPace: Casual\n\nDistance: 7 miles\n\nLeader
 : David Barish\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Christmas%20Lights%20Di
 splays.jpgThe Skokie Bike Network has revived the old EBC Holiday Lights R
 ide.\n\nThe ride leaves at 4pm from Sketchbook Brewery and Taproom \, 4901
  Main St.\, Skokie: https://www.sketchbookbrewing.com/skokie. We will take
  the Valley Line trail to Pratt and then to Longmeadow and the neighborhoo
 d where all the light displays will be. It is a short ride of just a few m
 iles but the lights are much better from a bike than from a car. When we g
 et back to Sketchbook we can debate which display was the best over a loca
 l beverage. Come join us!\n\nhttps://skokiebikenet.org/\n\n
LOCATION:Sketchbook Brewery & Taproom\, 4901 Main St.\, Skokie
CATEGORIES:..Casual (10-12 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
