BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Evanston Bike Club": "https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/BurlingtonWI-2.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png:"}
X-SOURCE-ID:evanston_bike_club
X-SOURCE:Evanston Bike Club
URL:https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/BurlingtonWI-2.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png:
UID:TU2023025234
DTSTAMP:20260315T011111Z
SUMMARY:Burlington Wisconsin Scenic Cruise (Peter Glaser)
DESCRIPTION:Status: CHANGES PENDING!\n\nPace: Fast\n\nDistance: 60 miles\n\
 nLeader: Peter Glaser\n\n**!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/BurlingtonWI-2
 .jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/RWGPS-route.png: https://ridewithgps.
 com/routes/43633474The FAST group (15-17mph) leaves Bristol Woods at 09:00
 AM.**  \nRemote Start: Bristol_Woods_County_Park: https://maps.google.com/
 maps?q=Bristol+Woods+County+Park\,+Bristol\,+WI&hl=en&sll=39.739318\,-89.2
 66507&sspn=15.139708\,33.815918&oq=brist&hq=Bristol+Woods+County+Park\,+Br
 istol\,+WI&t=m&z=15.Take I-94 North. A few miles past the Wisconsin border
 \, take Exit #347 Hwy 165/Cty Q. Turn left (west) at the end of the exit r
 amp and go west 2.5 miles on Qty Q.Turn right (north) at Cty MB and go 0.5
  miles. Turn left into the park entrance.Park at the Pringle Nature Center
  - follow the park road about 1/4 mile past the picnic shelter at the top 
 of the hill. Allow an hour from Evanston.  \nThere will be some rolling hi
 lls and maybe a few not so rolling. Most of the route is on scenic rural r
 oads. Lunch will be at a lovely cafe in Burlington - The Coffee House at C
 hestnut &amp\; Pine. We will also stop for root beer floats at the Dairy Q
 ueen in Silver Lake.\n\n*If weather is questionable check the Rides Forum 
 after 7:30 AM.*\n\n
LOCATION:Bristol Woods County Park\, Wisconsin
CATEGORIES:.Fast (15-17 mph)
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20270627T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20270627T090000
CREATED:20260112T230617Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260302T193245Z
RRULE:FREQ=YEARLY;BYMONTH=6;BYDAY=-1SU
X-TEAMUP-STATUS:CHANGES PENDING!
X-TEAMUP-PACE:Fast
X-TEAMUP-DISTANCE:60 miles
X-TEAMUP-START-LOCATION:Bristol Woods County Park\, Wisconsin
X-TEAMUP-LEADER:Peter Glaser
END:VEVENT
