BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Evanston Bike Club": "https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Glenview%20Rd%20House%20825.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Paris%20Baguette.jpgThis"}
X-SOURCE-ID:evanston_bike_club
X-SOURCE:Evanston Bike Club
URL:https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Glenview%20Rd%20House%20825.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Paris%20Baguette.jpgThis
UID:TU2023025246
DTSTAMP:20260315T011111Z
SUMMARY:A Tasty Ride Thru Glenview (Bruce Miller)
DESCRIPTION:Status: CHANGES PENDING!\n\nPace: Casual\n\nDistance: 21 Miles\
 n\nLeader: Bruce Miller\n\n!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Glenview%20Rd%
 20House%20825.jpg!https://ebcrides.org/images/cal/Paris%20Baguette.jpgThis
  week’s Thursday Casual ride: a meander through Glenview. Our destinatio
 n will be Paris Baguette and their yummy pastries. Along the way we’ll s
 top at 4 sites:\n\nA house that claims to be “America’s original solar
  home”\n\nA Mediterranean Revival estate formerly owned by David Smart\,
  publisher of Esquire and Coronet\n\nA classic Midcentury Modern house by 
 architect Don Erickson\n\n“The Park”\, a church-inspired subdivision\n
 \nJoin us for a Casual paced 21-mile loop\, departing from Chandler-Newber
 ger in Evanston at 9:00am. If necessary\, a ride cancellation will be post
 ed before 8:00am Thursday. Hope to see you!\n\nRWGPS  gps.com/routes/49961177\n\n
LOCATION:Chandler Park\, Evanston
CATEGORIES:..Casual (10-12 mph),.Weekly > ...Casual Wkly
CLASS:PUBLIC
TRANSP:OPAQUE
SEQUENCE:0
